{"lemma":"غَيْثِ","slug":"غَيْثِ","root":"غ.#.ث","root_slug":"غ-_-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-_-ث","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غَيْث","root":"غيث","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32698","n32700","n32702"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%AB%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rain","examples":[{"text":"جَادَكَ ٱلْغَيْثُ إِذَا ٱلْغَيْثُ هَمَا\n يَا زَمَانَ ٱلْوَصْلِ بِٱلْأَنْدَلُسِ\n لَمْ يَكُنْ وَصْلُكَ إِلَّا حُلُمًا\n فِي ٱلْكَرَى أَوْ خِلْسَةَ ٱلْمُخْتَلِسِ","english":"the rain would befit you if the rain fell\n oh the time of reunion in Andalusia\n your reunion wasn't but a dream\n in the sleep or a surreptitious passing (= something that passes quickly)"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣajθ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32698","headword_ar":"غيّث","root":"gyv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", said of a blind man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"searched,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"groped, with the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, TA:) also written ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ey~v","text_ar":"عيّث"},{"kind":"text","text":"] with [the unpointed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":", and thus correctly, though ISd thought this latter to be a mistranscription. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Kr","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n32700","headword_ar":"غَيْثٌ","root":"gyv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAva","text_ar":"غَاثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, O, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And [a subst.] signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain that occupies the space of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariyd","text_ar":"بَرِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six miles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twelve miles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in width:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain that is productive of much good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[supposed to belong to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gwv","text_ar":"غوث"},{"kind":"text","text":", for it is added,] because mankind are aided thereby; thus expl. in the “ Sharh esh-Shifè: ” pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agoyaAvN","text_ar":"اَغْيَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guyuwvN","text_ar":"غُيُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence a tropical usage in a saying mentioned voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaj~aAjN","text_ar":"ثَجَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbu gayovK","text_ar":"ذُبَابُ غَيْثٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbu Algayovi","text_ar":"ذُبَابُ الغَيْثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fly of rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fly of the rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bees"},{"kind":"text","text":"collectively: so called because the bee seeks after herbage and flowers, which are consequent upon the rain: (IAth, TA:) [for] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayovN","text_ar":"غَيْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, A, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which grows by means of the water of the sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, O, K:) called thus by the name of its cause. (Msb.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwqapN","text_ar":"فَرُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","Msb","K","AA","IAth","TA","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n32702","headword_ar":"غَيِّثٌ","root":"gyv","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayolamu maA='K","text_ar":"عَيْلَمُ مَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that is beneath a stratum of rock"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^orN *aAtu gay~ivK","text_ar":"بِيْرٌ ذَاتُ غَيِّثٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well having a constant accession of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b2-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN *uw gay~ivK","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ ذُو غَيِّثٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that performs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that increases"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his running"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"run after run."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}